		<div id="comment_body_64436840"><p>The "real world" places may check your ID but do not record it (and they won't usually check IDs at all if the customer is obviously an adult). There may be a tech solution to prevent recording the ID, but that assumes these laws are being passed in good faith (or will always be used in a good-faith manner). The problem is that that once this infrastructure is in place, it can be used to restrict all sorts of sites that the government simply doesn't like.</p></div>
	</div>

